      "system": {
        "lvl": 3,
        "class": "Cleric",
        "duration": "Permanent",
        "range": "Touch",
        "roll": "",
        "description": "<p><strong>Duration: Instant / Permanent (curse)</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Range: The caster or a creature touched</strong></p>\n<p>Remove curse instantaneously removes one curse from a creature. It may allow a character to discard a cursed magic item.</p>\n<p><strong>Reversed: Curse</strong></p>\n<p>Places a deleterious effect upon a creature, if it fails a Mental save.</p>\n<p><strong>▶ Effects: </strong>The exact form and effects of the curse are determined by the caster.</p>\n<p><strong>▶ Maximum possible effects include:</strong> A &ndash;2 penalty to saving throws, a &ndash;4 penalty to hit, reducing an ability score by 50%.</p>\n<p><strong>▶ Multiple curses: </strong>May afflict a creature, as long as each has a different effect.</p>\n<p><strong>▶ Referee judgement:</strong> The referee should judge the effects of this spell and may turn overly powerful curses back onto the caster!</p>",
        "prepared": true,
        "cast": 0,
        "save": "mental"
      },
