    {
      "_id": "v5ltDCQo22XKEYyb",
      "name": "Quest",
      "type": "spell",
      "sort": 2000000,
      "flags": {
        "cf": null,
        "core": {
          "sourceId": "Compendium.wwn.ose-spells.s8WcK2EHXsnz8Nft"
        }
      },
      "img": "systems/wwn/assets/default/spell.png",
      "effects": [],
      "system": {
        "lvl": 5,
        "class": "Cleric",
        "duration": "Indefinite",
        "range": "30'",
        "roll": "",
        "description": "<p><strong>Duration: Until quest is completed / </strong><strong>Instant (remove quest)</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Range: 30&rsquo;</strong></p>\n<p>The caster commands a single subject to perform a specific quest or task.</p>\n<p><strong>▶ Examples:</strong> Rescuing a prisoner, killing a specific monster, bringing a magic item to the caster, or going on a journey to a holy site.</p>\n<p><strong>▶ Suicidal quests:</strong> The prescribed quest must not be obviously suicidal.</p>\n<p><strong>▶ Saving throw: </strong>The subject may make a Mental save, with success indicating that the quest has no effect.</p>\n<p><strong>▶ Refusal:</strong> Otherwise, the subject must undertake the quest or fall under a curse (per the curse spell, with the exact nature of the curse determined by the referee).</p>\n<p><strong>▶ Completion:</strong> Once the task is completed, the spell ends.</p>\n<p><strong>Reversed: Remove Quest</strong></p>\n<p>Can dispel an active quest spell. If the character who cast the quest spell to be nullified is higher level than the character casting remove quest, there is a chance of the spell having no effect. The probability of failure is 5% per level the caster is below the caster of quest.</p>",
        "prepared": true,
        "cast": 0,
        "save": "mental"
      },
